data.text:
Tel Aviv-Yafo, Israel

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 32.109333, 34.855499.

Tel Aviv-Yafo is one of the largest cities in Israel, the largest resort city and one of the most important tourist destinations in the Middle East. The city is located in the north western and the coastal part of the country. It is facing the Mediterranean Sea and marks the easternmost coasts of the sea. Tel Aviv lays in the lowlands and has a very interesting location, right on the broad border between three continents, Europe, Asia and Africa. The city is situated about 45 miles north west of Jerusalem, the capital city of Israel. The distance between Tel Aviv and the Dead Sea is about 55 miles, and the distance from Tel Aviv to the city of Amman is about 70 miles. The Stripe of Gaza is located about 65 miles south west of the city of Tel Aviv.

There is one more large metropolitan zone, the city of Yafo (Yaffa) located to the north of Tel Aviv city center. Together with its numerous neighborhoods and towns located on the outskirts, Tel Aviv forms the metropolitan area known as the Gush Dan. It has a very impressive area of about 600 square miles. The close neighborhoods of Tel Aviv include the districts of Petah Tikva, Ramat Gan, Holon, Bnei Brak, Bat Yam, Yehud, Sarona, Rishon LeTsiyon, and plenty of more. The river of Yarkon is passing across the northern part of the city and there is the main green area around the river which can be found just a mile north of the city center. Two important national resorts and cities, Ashkelon and Ashdod, are located to the sheer south of Tel Aviv, in the southern coastal region of Israel.
